'''s'Too Vees''', a [[Human/Legends|Human]], was a [[Gambling/Legends|gambler]] who was present in the [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]] [[Mining/Legends|mining]] complex of [[Cloud City/Legends|Cloud City]] during the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] [[Occupation of Bespin|subjugation]] of the [[City/Legends|city]] in [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]]. Vees evacuated Bespin and followed former Cloud City [[Baron Administrator/Legends|Baron Administrator]] [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] to the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]]. Vees rose to the [[Military rank/Legends|rank]] of [[Lieutenant/Legends|lieutenant]] and served the Alliance as a [[Hangar/Legends|dock]] [[Technician/Legends|mechanic]]. In [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], he operated a [[CS-Mark 12 holoprojector|holoprojector]] during the briefing before the Alliance's [[Battle of Endor/Legends|attack]] on the [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]]. Vees intentionally turned down an opportunity to serve in the rear guard in order to work on Calrissian's [[Starship/Legends|starship]], the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']].

==Biography==
[[File:STooVees-ROTJ.jpg|thumb|right|250px|s'Too Vees operates the holoprojector on ''Home One''.]]
The [[Human/Legends|Human]]<ref name="ROTJ" /> [[Gambling/Legends|gambler]] s'Too Vees was present in [[Cloud City/Legends|Cloud City]],<ref name="CCG">{{CCG|set=Death Star II Limited|cardname=Lieutenant s'Too Vees}}</ref> a [[Tibanna/Legends|Tibanna gas]] [[Mining/Legends|mining]] [[City/Legends|colony]] of the [[Gas giant/Legends|gas giant]] [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]], by<ref name="ESB">{{Film|V}}</ref> [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]].<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the [[occupation of Bespin]] to [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]].</ref> When [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] forces under the command of the [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] [[Occupation of Bespin|seized control]] of Bespin<ref name="ESB" /> in that [[Standard year/Legends|year]],<ref name="NEC" /> Cloud City [[Baron Administrator/Legends|Baron Administrator]] [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] ordered the evacuation of his complex.<ref name="ESB" /> Vees followed Calrissian from Cloud City and joined the [[Military rank/Legends|ranks]] of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]], where he found work as a [[Hangar/Legends|dock]] [[Technician/Legends|mechanic]], installing [[Cannon/Legends|cannons]] on [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighters]] and eventually attaining the rank of [[Lieutenant/Legends|lieutenant]].<ref name="CCG" />

In [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]],<ref name="RotJ date">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' establishes that the events of [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']] take place in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]].</ref> when the Rebel Alliance learned of the location of the Empire's new [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]] [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]], in construction over the [[Endor/Legends|Forest Moon of Endor]], the [[Alliance High Command/Legends|Alliance command]] devised a plan to destroy the [[Space station/Legends|station]] before its construction could be completed.<ref name="ROTJ" /> In a briefing aboard the [[MC80A Home One Type Heavy Star Cruiser/Legends|Mon Calamari Star Cruiser]] [[Home One/Legends|''Home One'']], [[Flagship/Legends|flagship]] of the [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|Alliance Fleet]], Vees operated a [[CS-Mark 12 holoprojector|holoprojector]] illustrating the plan for the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|upcoming battle]]: a [[Endor strike team/Legends|Rebel strike team]] would deactivate the [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star's]] [[Endor shield generator bunker|deflector shield]] on the Endor [[Moon/Legends|moon]], and then a starfighter force would fly into the battlestation and destroy its [[Hypermatter reactor/Legends|main reactor]].<ref name="ROTJ" />

Calrissian, having been promoted to [[General/Legends|general]], would lead the fighter assault.<ref name="ROTJ" /> In preparations for the battle, Vees was offered an assignment in the rear guard but turned it down in order to work on Calrissian's [[Starship/Legends|starship]],<ref name="CCG" /> the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']], borrowed from Rebel General [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], who was leading the Endor ground assault team.<ref name="ROTJ" />

==Personality and traits==
Vees,<ref name="CCG" /> like Calrissian,<ref name="ESB" /> was a gambler.<ref name="CCG" /> When Calrissian left Cloud City in order to escape the Imperial occupation,<ref name="ESB" /> Vees followed him, joining the Rebel Alliance. Later, when Vees was offered a position in the rear guard, he turned it down in favor of working on Calrissian's vessel.<ref name="CCG" /> He was light-skinned and had [[Color/Legends|brown]] [[Hair/Legends|hair]].<ref name="ROTJ" />

==Skills and abilities==
Vees could operate a [[Holoprojector/Legends|holoprojector]].<ref name="ROTJ" />

==Equipment==
During the briefing before the Battle of Endor, Vees wore brown [[Clothing/Legends|clothing]] and a headset while operating the holoprojector.<ref name="ROTJ" />

==Behind the scenes==
The character s'Too Vees first appeared as an unnamed and uncredited extra in the [[1983]] film [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']], in which he is shown at the controls for the holoprojector during the Rebel briefing before the Battle of Endor.<ref name="ROTJ" /> His name and additional details were provided on the [http://www.starwarsccg.org/cardlists/images/starwars/DeathStarII-Light/large/lieutenantstoovees.gif "Lieutenant s'Too Vees" card] for the [[July]] [[2000]] ''[[Death Star II Limited]]'' expansion set of the [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]].<ref name="CCG" />

